{{!--
  Template: agent-prompt.md.hbs
  Context:  PerAgentContext (context: "agent")

  Available variables:
    agent                - Agent object with id, role_name, purpose, mode, dispatch_only,
                           can_read_artifacts, can_write_artifacts, can_execute_tools,
                           can_invoke_agents, can_return_handoffs, responsibilities,
                           constraints, rules, anti_patterns, escalation_criteria,
                           prerequisites, and any x-* extension properties
    receivableTasks      - Array of tasks where target_agent == this agent (each has id)
    delegatableTasks     - Array of tasks this agent can invoke on other agents
                           (id, description, target_agent, workflow, input_artifacts,
                            invocation_handoff, result_handoff,
                            invocation_payload_keys, result_payload_keys)
    relatedArtifacts     - Record<id, Artifact> this agent can read/write
    relatedTools         - Record<id, Tool> this agent can execute
    relatedHandoffTypes  - Record<kind, HandoffType> related to this agent's tasks/handoffs
    mergedBehavior       - Agent + all receivable tasks merged:
                           responsibilities, constraints, rules, anti_patterns,
                           escalation_criteria, execution_steps, completion_criteria
    dsl                  - Full DSL object for cross-referencing

  Custom helpers:
    notEmpty             - {{#if (notEmpty obj)}} — true when obj has at least one key
    inc                  - {{inc @index}} — 1-based index (0 → 1, 1 → 2, ...)
    eq                   - {{#if (eq a b)}} — strict equality
    yamlBlock            - {{{yamlBlock obj}}} — render object as YAML text
    lookupPayloadFields  - {{#each (lookupPayloadFields payload)}} — extract field info

  Notes:
    - Record objects (relatedArtifacts, relatedTools, relatedHandoffTypes) use
      {{@key}} to access the record key and {{this.*}} for properties.
    - Use (notEmpty ...) instead of .length to check if a Record has entries.
    - Arrays (receivableTasks, delegatableTasks) support .length directly.
--}}
